cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with speech recognition in mixed language, which falls under the domain of natural language processing. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with speech recognition. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a CTC-based end-to-end automatic speech recognition model. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with developing a model for speech recognition. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with language transitions in code-switching, which can be seen as a social phenomenon.
